  "body": "### Discussed in https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/discussions/28080\r\n\r\n<div type='discussions-op-text'>\r\n\r\n<sup>Originally posted by **vladaman** September 20, 2022</sup>\r\nWe have integrated AWS API Gateway HTTP API + Cognito and JWT. When we include `Bearer` keyword in Authorization header we get 401 error from Quarkus.\r\n\r\nReturns 401 error\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X 'GET' \\\r\n  'https://api.mysite.com/0.5/app-user/heyho' \\\r\n  -H 'accept: application/json' \\\r\n  -H 'Authorization: Bearer eyJraWQiOiJ1aVcwcxxxxx'\r\n```\r\nResponse:\r\n```\r\n< HTTP/2 401 \r\n< date: Tue, 20 Sep 2022 08:03:32 GMT\r\n< content-length: 0\r\n< www-authenticate: Bearer\r\n< apigw-requestid: Yv8JOgAWhAcEMpQ=\r\n```\r\n\r\nFollowing call succeeds (_note, Bearer keyword is not included_) but JsonWebToken is null:\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X 'GET' \\\r\n  'https://api.mysite.com/0.5/app-user/heyho' \\\r\n  -H 'accept: application/json' \\\r\n  -H 'Authorization: eyJraWQiOiJ1aVcwcxxxxx'\r\n```\r\n\r\napplication.properties:\r\n```\r\nquarkus.lambda-http.enable-security=true\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow do I configure Quarkus to accept Authorization header via AWS API Gateway if it includes \"Bearer\"?</div>",
